s005-mozilla-tutorial
Mozilla tutorial borderify.

s007-reqwest
Using Rust library reqwest. A sample result (from WSWS) in result.txt.

s008-readfile
Program reads the whole contents of a text file to memory.

s009-scrape
Use scraper to parse HTML. Use method html to get the whole
document content.

s010-meilisearch
Beginnings of search with meilisearch. Abandoned: I will
try tantivy, because I don't want a backend server at the
moment.

s011-tantivy
Basic search using Tantivy.

s012-parse-html
Parsing an HTML document with scraper.

s013-parse-bookmarks
Parsing HTML bookmark files with scraper. Abandoned - I will
try with html5ever.

s014-parse-html5ever
Scan input HTML file using html5ever and sample from that project's
repository that outputs tokens (HTML tags, CHAR data, etc.).

s015-bookmark-parser
Parse bookmark file input.html using netscape_bookmark_parser. Doesn't
work.

s016-bookmarkt
Using bookmarkt for scanning bookmarks.html. Abandoned.
Removed - bookmarkt is GPL.

s017-scan
Scanning one-line HTML file with html5ever.

s018-readlines
Read text file line by line.

s019-scan-bookmarks
Scan bookmarks file with html5ever and print HTML tokens (start/end
tags (names/attributes), text).

s020-scan-to-tokens
Parsing text file line by line and generating a vector of tokens; each
token can be for start tag, end tag and text. Using a vector for
storing a tag's attributes. Next: move to using a mapping key -> value.

s021-map
Exploring HashMap to store a map string -> string.

s022-attribute-map
From s020-scan-to-tokens: tag attributes are now stores as a mapping
key -> value (HashMap<String, String>).

s023-stack
Stack of strings implemented as a Vec<String>.

s024-bookmarks
Process bookmarks file (input.html) and store and print bookmarks.

s025-web-page-search
Fetch one web page, create Tantivy index, search for a phrase in the index
and display the result.

s026-cmdline
Parse command line parameters using clap. Parameters supported are --index
and --url.

s027-parse-web-page
Download a web page and extract its title.

s028-cmdline-bookmarks
Two command line programs: write-search that downloads web pages and indexes
them and search that searches for a query in the index.

s029-bookmark-search
Read bookmarks, download and index pages, search.
TODO: web page cleanup (html2text, readibility), showing snippets in search
results, incremental indexing of the most recent bookmarks, letting user of
search specify how many results he wants to see, web interface.

s030-html2text
Convert HTML file to plain text and display.

s031-fast_html2md
Convert HTMLfile to markdown using s031-fast_html2md.

s032-calculate-time
Calculate the number of days from a specified epoch timestamp to now using chrono.

s033-bookmarks-with-datetime
Added field add_date to bookmark item.

s035-parse-u32
Parse string to u32.

s036-timestamp
Convert timestamp as string to DateTime (UTC time), then calculate the number of
days from that time to now.

s037-bookmarks-datetime
Added field last_modified and remove add_date in bookmarks. Update code to read
last_modified from bookmark file.

s038-bookmarks-incremental
From s037, indexing and searching works. Bookmark contains last_modified.
TODO: add href in the index.

s039-bookmarks-with-href
Storing the href (URL) with each bookmark.

s040-is-dir
Using std::fs to check if a file exists and whether it is a directory or
regular file.

s041-create-if-not-file
If "./index" is a regular file, report error. If it is a directory, do nothing and
report success. If it doesn't exist, create as a directory and report success.

s042-create-index-dir
Program gets command line parameter: --index <index-dir> and tries to create the
index directory. If the path alrady exists, but it is a regular file, exit with
error message.

s043-process-bookmarks
From s042: added --bookmarks and code for reading and parsing bookmarks file.
For now just displaying parsed information.

s044-print-bookmarks
From s044: parsing bookmarks into a vector of bookmark items and printing all the
items in the vector.

s045-max-age
Added command line parameter max_age. Scanner adds a bookmark to the vector of
bookmarks only if it is not older than max_age. max_age can be empty, in which case
all bookmarks are added to the vector. Other items (folder and unfolder) are
always added to the vector of bookmarks.

s046-clap-subcommands
Small program to use clap to implement two subcommands write and search.

s047-write-subcommand
from s045 and s046: writing index is now a clap subcommand.

s048-search-subcommand
from s047: searching in the index is now a clap subcommand. Extracted creating
Tantivy schema to function create_schema, which is called from both write_index and
search.

s049-optimizing
Created struct Indexer for indexing, which has separate methods write and commit.
The purpose is to enable indexing multiple bookmarks before committing, in order
to speed up the operation.

s050-occasional-commit
Only do commit to disk on every ten index writes.

s051-input-mbs
Code that parses size that can be expressed in raw number, a number of KB, MB or
GB. For example: 10000, 10KB, 20MB, 1GB.

s052-cmdline
Added two more command line parameters to write subcommand: commit_period and
memory_budget. commit_period defines how often we do commit, and memory_budget is
the memory budget passed to index.writer.

s053-status-bar
Show download status using status_line crate.

s054-status-indicatif
Show status using indicatif.

s055-bookmark-indicatif
From s052-cmdline. While indexing, show progress using indicatif.

s056-test-rayon
Running function do_work in a thread pool using Rayon. Each run of do_work sleeps
for a random time and then exits.

s057-rayon-send-result
From s056, but do_work returns a string that is sent back on a channel. Main thread
runs another thread that receives all the results.

s058-rayon-join
From s057, but we also get a join handle from spawn and then join that handle before
finishing.

s059-bookmark-rayon
Beginning of code using rayon to index bookmarks in parallel. Postponed; first I
have to work out using rayon to send a structure through a channel to another
thread.

s060-rayon-send-struct
From s058; we send an instance of a struct though the channel.

s061-bookmark-rayon
From s059-bookmark-rayon. Using a thread pool with the size 20. The whole set of
~3400 bookmarks is index in 5min 49sec (down from 42min). TODO: the code is hacky,
clean up and refactor. The size of the thread pool is now hard-coded.

s062-indexer
From s061-bookmark-rayon: reorganized so Indexer::index creates all the threads
needed to run indexing.

s063-write-params
Made write subcommand's parameters work as expected: if --commit-period is not
provided on the command line, the default is 0, which means the indexer only
commits once, at the end of indexing all bookmarks in memory.

s064-parse-json
Parse JSON with serde.

s065-tidy-search-output
For write command, added command-line parameter --threads for the number of threads
in the indexing worker pool. For search command, added command-line parameter
--num-result for the number of search results to display. Added url field for
indexing the bookmark's URL. Tidied the search result output.

s066-sqlite3
Using SQLite3 from Python3.

s067-rusqlite
Using SQLite3 from Rust.

s068-bookmark-db
Create a bookmark database, insert one record and query and list all records
in the database.

s069-bookmark-db
From s068. Extracted database operations into separate module bookmarkdb.rs.

s070-db-api
From s070. Cleaned up database operations. Renamed insert_db to insert. Added
exists.

s071-read-toml
Read a TOML file using toml crate.

s072-readconfig
Read configuration file name from command line, open the configuration file
and parse it, and print the configuration.
